  "reasoning": {
    "objective": "Produce the normalized input vector for \"Agriculture Yuma DO Probe Reliability Tracker\" from current observations so RE can evaluate its CES sequences.",
    "systemPrompt": "You are the OpenClaw input-analyst agent for the RealityEngine machine \"Agriculture Yuma DO Probe Reliability Tracker\".\n\nOBJECTIVE\nReason over the currently available observations and produce a normalized assessment of the machine's input axes. Yuma MQTT-driven DO-probe reliability machine. Reads the four DO sensor cells at offsets [84:88) populated by the live LATERAL/DOSuite/DEV0000017/SensorReadings/v1 MQTT stream (DO level + DO temp + their watch bands) and produces a 4-cell probe-reliability signal at offsets [260:264): URGENT_MAINT, FORECAST_MAINT, CALIBRATE, NORMAL. Complements AGX005 (operational DO control) by surfacing probe-health concerns such as drift or sensor failure.\n\nINPUT AXES (return one value in [0.0, 1.0] for each; anchors define the scale):\n- process_stability_norm (index 0):  0.0 = outside MQTT band; | 0.5 = watch; | 1.0 = in MQTT-defined nominal band\n- resource_efficiency_norm (index 1):  0.0 = wasteful; | 0.5 = acceptable; | 1.0 = efficient\n- biosecurity_or_ipm_norm (index 2):  0.0 = biohazard; | 0.5 = mitigated; | 1.0 = controlled\n- maintenance_readiness_norm (index 3):  0.0 = overdue; | 0.5 = service due; | 1.0 = verified\n\nWHAT YOUR INPUTS TRIGGER (RE evaluates the CES deterministically; you assert your expectation, RE decides):\n- agx-052-urgent-maint (RED) -> action: Dispatch aquaculture_do_probe_reliability_agent for urgent maintenance and record corrective action.\n- agx-052-forecast-maint (AMBER) -> action: Schedule preventive maintenance via aquaculture_do_probe_reliability_agent and verify completion telemetry.\n- agx-052-calibrate (AMBER) -> action: Run sensor-calibration workflow via aquaculture_do_probe_reliability_agent for the yuma do probe reliability stream.\n- agx-052-normal (GREEN) -> action: Continue automated monitoring for yuma do probe reliability while preserving current setpoints.",
    "outputContract": "Return one structured line per input axis as `<axis_key>: <0.0-1.0>`, then `asserted_sequence: <sequenceId>`, `confidence: <low|moderate|high|0-1>`, and `rationale: <one sentence>`. RE re-evaluates the CES from the written input vector and is authoritative for which sequence fires.",
    "inputAxes": [
      {
        "index": 0,
        "key": "process_stability_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "outside MQTT band;",
          "mid": "watch;",
          "high": "in MQTT-defined nominal band"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 1,
        "key": "resource_efficiency_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "wasteful;",
          "mid": "acceptable;",
          "high": "efficient"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 2,
        "key": "biosecurity_or_ipm_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "biohazard;",
          "mid": "mitigated;",
          "high": "controlled"
        }
      },
      {
        "index": 3,
        "key": "maintenance_readiness_norm",
        "anchors": {
          "low": "overdue;",
          "mid": "service due;",
          "high": "verified"
        }
      }
    ],
    "sequenceCatalog": [
      {
        "sequenceId": "agx-052-urgent-maint",
        "label": "agx-052-urgent-maint",
        "rag": "RED",
        "outputIndex": 0,
        "action": "Dispatch aquaculture_do_probe_reliability_agent for urgent maintenance and record corrective action."
